      • betweenUnique

        default E betweenUnique(V from,
                        V to)
        If there is exactly one edge between the provided vertices, this edge is returned. If there is no edge between the provided vertices, null is returned. If there are multiple edges between them, an exception is thrown.
        Parameters:
        from - The tail vertex of the edge
        to - The head vertex of the edge
        Returns:
        The edge between the given head and tail, or null if no such edge exists.
